  "prompt": "What are the Upcoming mobiles?",
  "response": "The smartphone market is constantly evolving, with new models being announced and released frequently. Here are some **upcoming mobile phones** that were highly anticipated as of **October 2023**, along with some expected launches based on trends and rumors. Keep in mind that release dates and features may vary, so it's always best to check official sources for the latest updates.\n\n---\n\n### **Upcoming Smartphones (Late 2023 - Early 2024)**\n\n#### **1. Apple iPhone 15 Series**  \n   - **Expected Release**: Already launched in September 2023, widely available.  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - USB-C port (first for iPhones).  \n     - Dynamic Island across all models.  \n     - A17 Bionic chip (iPhone 15 Pro models).  \n     - Titanium design (Pro models).  \n\n#### **2. Google Pixel 8 Series**  \n   - **Expected Release**: Already launched in October 2023, available in stores.  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - Tensor G3 chip.  \n     - Enhanced AI features like Magic Editor and AI-powered Zoom.  \n     - 7 years of software updates.  \n     - Improved cameras with Pro-level features.  \n\n#### **3. Samsung Galaxy S24 Series**  \n   - **Expected Release**: January 2024 (rumored).  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 or Exynos 2400 (region-dependent).  \n     - Improved AI capabilities.  \n     - Enhanced cameras with better low-light performance.  \n     - Design refinements and possibly flat edges.  \n\n#### **4. OnePlus 12**  \n   - **Expected Release**: December 2023 or January 2024.  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 chip.  \n     - 120Hz AMOLED display with LTPO technology.  \n     - Hasselblad-tuned cameras.  \n     - Faster charging and improved battery life.  \n\n#### **5. Xiaomi 14 Series**  \n   - **Expected Release**: October 2023 (launch confirmed in China).  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 chip.  \n     - Leica-tuned cameras.  \n     - 2K AMOLED display with 120Hz refresh rate.  \n     - MIUI 15 based on Android 14.  \n\n#### **6. Motorola Edge 40 Neo**  \n   - **Expected Release**: Already launched in September 2023.  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - MediaTek Dimensity 7030 chip.  \n     - 144Hz pOLED display.  \n     - 50MP main camera.  \n     - Stylish design with vegan leather finish.  \n\n#### **7. Nothing Phone (2a)**  \n   - **Expected Release**: Early 2024 (rumored).  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - Affordable mid-range option.  \n     - Glyph Interface (LED lights on the back).  \n     - Clean Android-like Nothing OS.  \n\n#### **8. Oppo Find X7 Series**  \n   - **Expected Release**: Early 2024.  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 or Dimensity 9300 (depending on model).  \n     - Advanced camera setup with periscope zoom.  \n     - Fast charging (100W+).  \n\n#### **9. Vivo X100 Series**  \n   - **Expected Release**: November 2023 (rumored).  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - MediaTek Dimensity 9300 chip.  \n     - Zeiss-tuned cameras.  \n     - AMOLED display with high refresh rate.  \n\n#### **10. Honor Magic6 Series**  \n   - **Expected Release**: Early 2024.  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 chip.  \n     - High-refresh-rate OLED display.  \n     - Advanced camera system with AI features.  \n\n---\n\n### **Trends to Watch in Upcoming Phones**  \n   - **Foldable Phones**: Expect new models from Samsung (Galaxy Z Fold 6 and Z Flip 6), Xiaomi, and others in 2024.  \n   - **AI Integration**: Devices will increasingly focus on AI-driven features for photography, productivity, and personalization.  \n   - **Faster Charging**: Phones with 100W+ charging are becoming more common.  \n   - **Sustainability**: Brands like Apple, Samsung, and Google are focusing on eco-friendly designs and materials.  \n\n---\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, stay tuned to official announcements from manufacturers or trusted tech news sources. Let me know if you'd like details on a specific brand or model!",
